This is a careless mistake in the code (I think I'm the guilty party). Obviously 
the call to setName should go inside the if block.  Otherwise, if there is an 
IOException while reading, it will get the NullPointerException because the 
description will be null.  Here is the guilty code:

if (description != null && !isDefaultLocation)
	description.setLocation(projectLocation);
//don't trust the project name in the description file
description.setName(target.getName());
